The article discusses the importance of robust internet connectivity for various industries such as agriculture, manufacturing, small business, education, and healthcare. However, it points out that nearly 39 percent of rural Americans lack sufficient broadband access, creating a digital divide. The unique geography of rural America makes it more challenging and expensive to build secure broadband networks. The Trump administration has made it a priority to invest in the country's infrastructure and bring prosperity to rural America. The American Broadband Initiative report serves as a roadmap for federal departments to streamline permitting, leverage government assets, and maximize taxpayer funds to bring high-speed broadband networks to rural areas.